newsitem.title: USA: U.S. Northwest spot products notionally steady.
newsitem.headline: U.S. Northwest spot products notionally steady.

text.p: U.S. Northwest gasoline was notionally unchanged late Friday, in line with flat California material.
Regular unleaded gasoline was assessed at 68.00 cents to 69.00 cent a gallon, flat from Thursday.
Premium remained about six cents over regular.
Distillates also stayed flat, though traders saw prices ready to rise once cooler weather settles into the Pacific Northwest.
Low sulphur held around 74/75 cents a gallon in Seattle, while high sulphur maintained its typical two cent discount.
